cular-genetics","sex"],"score":4,"accepted_answer_id":15920,"down_vote_count":0,"is_answered":true,"view_count":405,"up_vote_count":4,"last_edit_date":1395164110},{"owner":{"profile_image":"https://i.stack.imgur.com/f0PGT.jpg?s=128&g=1","user_type":"registered","user_id":3615,"link":"http://biology.stackexchange.com/users/3615/biogirl","reputation":3923,"display_name":"biogirl","accept_rate":89},"answers":[{"owner":{"profile_image":"https://www.gravatar.com/avatar/476e67c92121154e7910301e56cdfc4c?s=128&d=identicon&r=PG","user_type":"registered","user_id":948,"link":"http://biology.stackexchange.com/users/948/mattdmo","reputation":7591,"display_name":"MattDMo","accept_rate":50},"score":3,"is_accepted":true,"comments":[{"owner":{"profile_image":"https://www.gravatar.com/avatar/da1e8af33e12bfa60ea44b3af00c0d03?s=128&d=identicon&r=PG&f=1","user_type":"moderator","user_id":5144,"link":"http://biology.stackexchange.com/users/5144/chris","reputation":31001,"display_name":"Chris"},"score":0,"post_id":15923,"edited":false,"creation_date":1395167951,"comment_id":21292,"body":"I agree with you, this paper offers a very good overview."}],"down_vote_count":0,"last_activity_date":1395252572,"creation_date":1395167607,"body":"<p>I'm just skimming through it now, but <a href=\"http://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pubmed/22193408\" rel=\"nofollow\">this 2011 review<\/a> in Nature Reviews Cancer looks like it has everything you could possibly want to know about the BRCA1/BRCA2 pathway. If you don't have access to the journal, the first page of <a href=\"https://www.google.com/#q=brca2+pathway\" rel=\"nofollow\">this Google search<\/a> should have a PDF link to Researchgate down near the bottom, or you can try <a href=\"http://www.google.com/url?sa=t&amp;rct=j&amp;q=&amp;esrc=s&amp;source=web&amp;cd=14&amp;ved=0CI4BEBYwDQ&amp;url=http%3A%2F%2Fwww.researchgate.net%2Fpublication%2F224824106_BRCA1_and_BRCA2_important_differences_with_common_interests%2Ffile%2F79e415106a30cd771d.pdf&amp;ei=6IooU7G