vely charged BRC repeat helical arches.The BRCA2 helix-turn-helix domain(red) at the end of the tower may bind dsDNA in cis at the ssDNA/dsDNA intra-DNA junction (3) or in trans to the dsDNA that later serves as the homologous DNA template (6) and the positively charged arch may also help to attract the dsDNA template. <\/p>\n\n<p>Source : Yang etal. 2002 , Shin et al 2003<\/p>\n\n<p>Thanks to Nicholas Provert for teaching me basics of PyMOL on Coursera.<\/p>\n","answer_id":15948,"question_id":15921,"up_vote_count":0}],"link":"http://biology.stackexchange.com/questions/15921/functioning-of-brca2","last_activity_date":1395254226,"creation_date":1395165615,"answer_count":2,"title":"Functioning of BRCA2","body":"<p>I know that <a href=\"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/BRCA2\" rel=\"nofollow\">BRCA2<\/a> interacts with RAD51 to repair DNA damage.<\/p>\n\n<p>But how exactly does it function ? What are the other proteins that interact with it ? <\/p>\n","question_id":15921,"tags":["dna","genetics","cancer"],"score":2,"accepted_answer_id":15923,"down_vote_count":0,"is_answered":true,"view_count":62,"up_vote_count":2},{"owner":{"profile_image":"https://www.gravatar.com/avatar/19a3374fef34dc09ea6e80a5b05c2d8f?s=128&d=identicon&r=PG&f=1","user_type":"registered","user_id":3141,"link":"http://biology.stackexchange.com/users/3141/laggingreflex","reputation":446,"display_name":"laggingreflex","accept_rate":93},"comments":[{"owner":{"profile_image":"https://www.gravatar.com/avatar/476e67c92121154e7910301e56cdfc4c?s=128&d=identicon&r=PG","user_type":"registered","user_id":948,"link":"http://biology.stackexchange.com/users/948/mattdmo","reputation":7591,"display_name":"MattDMo","accept_rate":50},"score":0,"post_id":15947,"edited":false,"creation_date":1395253650,"comment_id":21333,"body":"Snoring involves generating sound while inhaling, and people can speak while inhaling as well."},{"owner":{"profile_image":"https://www.gravatar.com/avatar/19a3374fef34dc09ea6e80a5b05c2d8f?s=128&d=id