 packed leaf sheaths, but the stem cannot be seen in your picture. <a href=\"http://www.promusa.org/tiki-index.php?page=Morphology+of+banana+plant\" rel=\"nofollow\">Here<\/a> is a webpage on banana morphology, if you want to get some further information.<\/p>\n\n<p>Some examples:<\/p>\n\n<p><img src=\"http://i.stack.imgur.com/GNLr0.jpg\" alt=\"enter image description here\">\n<img src=\"http://i.stack.imgur.com/tSAXo.jpg\" alt=\"enter image description here\"><\/p>\n","answer_id":15912,"question_id":15904,"up_vote_count":3,"last_edit_date":1395156161}],"link":"http://biology.stackexchange.com/questions/15904/what-is-this-plant","last_activity_date":1395156161,"creation_date":1395112502,"answer_count":1,"title":"What is this plant?","body":"<p>I really like this plant--I'm just wondering what its name is (perhaps genus+species). I think this plant grows in the tropical rainforest in Malaysia.<\/p>\n\n<p><img src=\"http://i.stack.imgur.com/QAlZd.jpg\" alt=\"enter image description here\"><\/p>\n\n<p>Any suggestions?<\/p>\n\n<p>Thanks!<\/p>\n","question_id":15904,"tags":["botany","species-identification"],"score":3,"accepted_answer_id":15912,"down_vote_count":0,"is_answered":true,"view_count":183,"up_vote_count":3,"last_edit_date":1395140796},{"owner":{"profile_image":"https://i.stack.imgur.com/f0PGT.jpg?s=128&g=1","user_type":"registered","user_id":3615,"link":"http://biology.stackexchange.com/users/3615/biogirl","reputation":3923,"display_name":"biogirl","accept_rate":89},"answers":[{"owner":{"profile_image":"https://www.gravatar.com/avatar/da1e8af33e12bfa60ea44b3af00c0d03?s=128&d=identicon&r=PG&f=1","user_type":"moderator","user_id":5144,"link":"http://biology.stackexchange.com/users/5144/chris","reputation":31001,"display_name":"Chris"},"score":1,"is_accepted":true,"down_vote_count":0,"last_activity_date":1395154364,"creation_date":1395154364,"body":"<p>This seems a bit like a hen and egg problem. Telomere length is both associated with age and with heart diseases, but heart disease is also associated with age. The question here is, is one really causing the other here (short telomeres heart problems) or do they occur simultaneously? The other problem with heart disease is that it is a multi-risk disease, with many risks accumulating with age. The figure below sums this up, it is from the first paper:<\/p>\n\n<p><img src=\"http://i.stack.imgur.com/LvjZH.jpg\" alt=\"enter image description here\"><\/p>\n\n<p>Have a look on these articles:<\/p>\n\n<ul>\n<li><a href=\"http://eurjhf.oxfordjournals.org/content/10/11/1049.full\" rel=\"nofollow\">Telomere biology in heart failure<\/a><\/li>\n<li><a href=\"http://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pubmed/20532978\" rel=\"nofollow\">Aging, telomeres and heart failure.<\/a><\/li>\n<li><a href=\"http://circres.ahajournals.org/content/94/5/575.full\" rel=\"nofollow\">Telomeres and Cardiovascular Disease<\/a><\/li>\n<\/ul>\n","answer_id":15911,"question_id":15910,"up_vote_count":1}],"link":"http://biology.stackexchange.com/questions/15910/association-of-shorter-telomeres-with-heart-disease","last_activity_date":1395154364,"creation_date":1395149445,"answer_count":1,"title":"Association of shorter telomeres with heart disease","body":"<p>From <a href=\"http://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pubmed/12573379\" rel=\"nofollow\">this<\/a> paper<\/p>\n\n<blockquote>\n  <p>Those with shorter telomeres in blood DNA had poorer survival,\n  attributable in part to a 3.18-fold higher mortality rate from heart\n  disease (95% CI 1(.)36-7.45, p=0.0079), and an 8.54-fold higher\n  mortality rate from infectious disease (1.52-47.9, p=0.015).<\/p>\n<\/blockquote>\n\n<p>What is the connection between shorter telomeres and heart disease ?<\/p>\n","question_id":15910,"tags":["human-biology","dna","cardiology","hematology","telomere"],"score":0,"accepted_answer_id":15911,"down_vote_count":0,"is_answered":true,"view_count":27,"up_vote_count":0},{"owner":{"profile_image":"https://www.gravatar.com/avatar/2e0ec0a72dc2fabef2d2eab4f85488