ty College London, Victor P. Whittaker eventually showed that the acetylcholine-rich particles derived from guinea-pig cerebral cortex were synaptic vesicle-rich pinched-off nerve terminals.  Whittaker coined the term synaptosome to describe these fractionation-derived particles and shortly thereafter synaptic vesicles could be isolated from lysed synaptosomes<\/p>\n<\/blockquote>\n","answer_id":10581,"question_id":10579,"up_vote_count":1,"last_edit_date":1380148763}],"link":"http://biology.stackexchange.com/questions/10579/what-is-the-full-name-of-e-g-gray","last_activity_date":1395153171,"creation_date":1380126615,"answer_count":1,"title":"What is the full name of E. G. Gray?","body":"<p>E. G. Gray is Neuro scientist who found and described first the two major morphologically defined synapse types (Gray Type I (asymmetric) and II (symmetric)) in his work \n<a href=\"http://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pmc/articles/PMC1244535/\" rel=\"nofollow\">E G Gray (Oct. 1959). \u201cAxo-somatic and axo-dendritic synapses of the cerebral cortex: an electron microscope study\u201d. In: Journal of Anatomy 93.4, pp. 420\u2013433<\/a><\/p>\n\n<p>However I am unable to find his full name nor further information about his life.<\/p>\n","question_id":10579,"tags":["neuroscience","history","synapses","scientific-literature"],"score":2,"accepted_answer_id":10581,"down_vote_count":0,"is_answered":true,"view_count":173,"up_vote_count":2,"last_edit_date":1395153171},{"owner":{"profile_image":"https://i.stack.imgur.com/qMiXK.jpg?s=128&g=1","user_type":"registered","user_id":3466,"link":"http://biology.stackexchange.com/users/3466/fbrundu","reputation":244,"display_name":"fbrundu","accept_rate":86},"comments":[{"owner":{"profile_image":"https://www.gravatar.com/avatar/79614cc5fcd376b95171a5c8f6354e8a?s=128&d=identicon&r=PG","user_type":"registered","user_id":5754,"link":"http://biology.stackexchange.com/users/5754/jarlemag","reputation":3075,"display_name":"jarlemag"},"score":0,"post_id":15502,"ed