me to 20.000 cells in your 8ml solution.<\/p>\n\n<p>When you want to know, how much of your solution you need, you calculate: $\\frac{2500 \\frac{cells}{ml}}{1000 cells} = \\frac{1 ml}{x}$. <\/p>\n\n<p>This can be transformed into $x = \\frac{1}{2,5} ml = 400 \\mu l$.<\/p>\n\n<p>So you need 400 $\\mu$l for each ml of your final cell solution. So if you want to have 5ml with 1000 cells/ml you need $5 \\times 400 \\mu l = 2000 \\mu l = 2 ml$ of your cell solution. To reach 5 ml add 3 ml of your solvent/media.<\/p>\n","answer_id":15770,"question_id":15769,"up_vote_count":1,"last_edit_date":1395041783},{"owner":{"profile_image":"https://i.stack.imgur.com/Kyg92.png?s=128&g=1","user_type":"registered","user_id":6061,"link":"http://biology.stackexchange.com/users/6061/rhill45","reputation":2493,"display_name":"rhill45","accept_rate":79},"score":1,"is_accepted":true,"comments":[{"owner":{"profile_image":"https://www.gravatar.com/avatar/1e66602058fade943f5dc8750998d56d?s=128&d=identicon&r=PG","user_type":"unregistered","user_id":6058,"link":"http://biology.stackexchange.com/users/6058/user6058","reputation":16,"display_name":"user6058"},"score":0,"post_id":15795,"edited":false,"creation_date":1395030849,"comment_id":21236,"body":"OMG! You should be a teacher!!  It&#39;s crystal clear now!  I&#39;m in love with this answer :)  Thank you very much. I wish you luck and success I sincerely do"}],"down_vote_count":0,"last_activity_date":1395025965,"creation_date":1395025965,"body":"<p>welcome to cell culture &amp; dimensional analysis<\/p>\n\n<p>125/50µl or 2.5 cells/µl is your concentration (better way of expressing it)<\/p>\n\n<p>2.5 * 8000µl = 20,000 total cells you have. 1000µl in 1ml that's why the 8000µl<\/p>\n\n<p>20,000 cells / 1000 cells/ml = 20mls final culture volume to reach desired concentration<\/p>\n\n<p>20mls - 8mls = 12mls   so you need to add 12mls of medium / saline / whatever to your 8mls to dilute it to the correct concentration.<\/p>\n\n<p>when you ask about solvent to ADD to make 5mls. Prob with this question is you don't state the desired concentration. So assuming its still 1000 cells/ml kinda go backwards,\n1000 cells/ml * 5mls = 5000 cells is what you want to get<\/p>\n\n<p>to get it:<\/p>\n\n<p>5000 / 2.5 cells/µl = 2000µl or 2mls of your culture.<\/p>\n\n<p>So take 2mls of your culture and mix it with 3mls of solvent / medium  (5mls - 2mls).<\/p>\n\n<p>I'm quite certain chris below is not correct.<\/p>\n","answer_id":15795,"question_id":15769,"up_vote_count":1}],"link":"http://biology.stackexchange.com/questions/15769/how-much-of-your-stock-solution-should-you-take-to-make-the-1000-cells-ml-mixtur","last_activity_date":1395041783,"creation_date":1395000547,"answer_count":2,"title":"How much of your stock solution should you take to make the 1000 cells/mL mixture?","body":"<p>You need a solution containing 1000 buccal cells/mL. You count that you have 125 buccal cells in 50uL, from a total solution of 8 mL. How much of your stock solution should you take to make the 1000 cells/mL mixture? How much solvent if you would like a total volume of 5mL?<\/p>\n\n<p>I don't even know how to approach this!!!\nHelp??<\/p>\n","question_id":15769,"tags":["homework"],"score":2,"accepted_answer_id":15795,"down_vote_count":0,"closed_reason":"off-topic","is_answered":true,"view_count":429,"up_vote_count":2},{"owner":{"profile_image":"https://www.gravatar.com/avatar/1e66602058fade943f5dc8750998d56d?s=128&d=identicon&r=PG","user_type":"unregistered","user_id":6058,"link":"http://biology.stackexchange.com/users/6058/user6058","reputation":16,"display_name":"user6058"},"answers":[{"owner":{"profile_image":"https://www.gravatar.com/avatar/889548c1e8387b3d381853dee5212cfd?s=128&d=identicon&r=PG","user_type":"registered","user_id":3632,"link":"http://biology.stackexchange.com/users/3632/shigeta","reputation":22684,"display_name":"shigeta","accept_rate":86},"score":1,"is_accepted":false,"comments":[{"owner":{"profile_image":"https://www.g