eir survival so they passed on the trait to their offspring. Ear topology didn't evolve in humans.<\/p>\n","answer_id":15655,"question_id":15553,"up_vote_count":1}],"link":"http://biology.stackexchange.com/questions/15553/what-is-the-evolutionary-purpose-of-the-topology-of-the-human-ear","last_activity_date":1394752160,"creation_date":1394168006,"answer_count":2,"title":"What is the evolutionary purpose of the topology of the human ear?","body":"<p>What is the evolutionary purpose of the topology of human ears? I understand why the ears may have a funnel-like shape but if the various \"hills and valleys\" do not amplify incoming sound, what purpose do they have?<\/p>\n","question_id":15553,"tags":["evolution","human-anatomy","hearing","human-ear"],"score":4,"accepted_answer_id":15647,"down_vote_count":0,"is_answered":true,"view_count":327,"up_vote_count":4,"last_edit_date":1394752160},{"owner":{"profile_image":"https://i.stack.imgur.com/anIxF.jpg?s=128&g=1","user_type":"registered","user_id":3657,"link":"http://biology.stackexchange.com/users/3657/katz","reputation":424,"display_name":"Katz","accept_rate":70},"answers":[{"owner":{"profile_image":"https://www.gravatar.com/avatar/da1e8af33e12bfa60ea44b3af00c0d03?s=128&d=identicon&r=PG&f=1","user_type":"moderator","user_id":5144,"link":"http://biology.stackexchange.com/users/5144/chris","reputation":31001,"display_name":"Chris"},"score":2,"is_accepted":true,"comments":[{"owner":{"profile_image":"https://i.stack.imgur.com/anIxF.jpg?s=128&g=1","user_type":"registered","user_id":3657,"link":"http://biology.stackexchange.com/users/3657/katz","reputation":424,"display_name":"Katz","accept_rate":70},"score":0,"post_id":15702,"edited":false,"creation_date":1394795711,"comment_id":21174,"body":"and when you make the calibration curve does it really matter which range of dilutions you choose or does it have to be a logarithmic serie? besides, when you get your results for different CTs, which is the criteria when choosing the c