airly complex communications. They run in packs, live with their mother for a number of years, and have a rather involved family structure that allows for the passing on of behaviors learned from previous generations. It would be difficult to tease out exactly which behaviors are instinctual, and which are learned, but you could say the same of humans as well.<\/p>\n","answer_id":15706,"question_id":15690,"up_vote_count":3}],"link":"http://biology.stackexchange.com/questions/15690/do-animals-follow-tactics","last_activity_date":1394724358,"creation_date":1394673391,"answer_count":1,"title":"Do animals follow tactics?","body":"<p>Are animals able to plan hunts, give tasks if they do it in groups and fulfil it adapted to the current situation? Do they use unique tactics for special circumstances (e.g. based on experiences)  or they just act from instincts?<\/p>\n","question_id":15690,"tags":["ethology"],"score":0,"accepted_answer_id":15706,"down_vote_count":0,"is_answered":true,"view_count":23,"up_vote_count":0},{"owner":{"profile_image":"https://www.gravatar.com/avatar/491c543d427efae88c29ebf1aa1a4e12?s=128&d=identicon&r=PG&f=1","user_type":"registered","user_id":5630,"link":"http://biology.stackexchange.com/users/5630/golgicik","reputation":148,"display_name":"golgicik","accept_rate":77},"comments":[{"owner":{"profile_image":"https://www.gravatar.com/avatar/889548c1e8387b3d381853dee5212cfd?s=128&d=identicon&r=PG","user_type":"registered","user_id":3632,"link":"http://biology.stackexchange.com/users/3632/shigeta","reputation":22684,"display_name":"shigeta","accept_rate":86},"score":0,"post_id":15679,"edited":false,"creation_date":1394633918,"comment_id":21126,"body":"flies aren&#39;t my field of expertise, but you probably would want to verify by PCR that any crosses were homozygous in any case."},{"owner":{"profile_image":"https://www.gravatar.com/avatar/491c543d427efae88c29ebf1aa1a4e12?s=128&d=identicon&r=PG&f=1","user_type":"registered","user_id":5630,"link":"http